13.60	Kanem_Empire	Kanem Empire	The Kanem Empire (ca. 600 BCE - 1380 CE) was located in the present countries of Chad, Nigeria and Libya. At its height it encompassed an area covering not only much of Chad, but also parts of southern Libya , northern Cameroon, eastern Niger and north-eastern Nigeria. The history of the Empire is mainly known from the Royal Chronicle or Dīwān discovered in 1851 by the German traveller Heinrich Barth.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a2/Afrika-Kanem-Bornu.png/250px-Afrika-Kanem-Bornu.png
